### For the entire SIM_cholesky_decomposition unit test directory ###

The S_define was set up to create a randomized 10x10 matrix.
Since the seeding is the same everytime for the matrix generation
it'll be the same for every single run even though it's random.

The "random seed matrix" is a lower diagonal of a 10x10 ranging in
values from 0 -> 3 with 4 significant digits.

The "random seed matrix" is multiplied by its transpose in order to
make "A-matrix (generated)".

Specific runs modify the "A-matrix (generated)" in specific ways in
order to create "A-matrix (modified)".

The cholesky decomposition is applied to "A-matrix (modified)" which
then creates "sqrt-A matrix".

The "sqrt-A matrix" is multiplied by its transpose in order to create
"B-matrix". If decomposition was done correctly then the "B-matrix"
should match "A-matrix (modified)".
